# Sunray Server — License Index

This repository contains Sunray Server software under **dual licensing**.
The applicable license depends on which addon you use.

| Addon | Tier | License | Full text |
|-------|------|---------|-----------|
| `project_addons/sunray_core/` | Free | **FSL-1.1-Apache-2.0** | [LICENSES/FSL-1.1-Apache-2.0.txt](LICENSES/FSL-1.1-Apache-2.0.txt) |
| `project_addons_advanced/sunray_advanced_core/` | Sunray Enterprise (paid) | **Elastic License 2.0 (ELv2)** | [LICENSES/ELv2.txt](LICENSES/ELv2.txt) |
| `project_addons_advanced/sunray_dashboard/` | Sunray Enterprise (paid) | **Elastic License 2.0 (ELv2)** | [LICENSES/ELv2.txt](LICENSES/ELv2.txt) |

## Plain-language summary

**Sunray Core (free tier)** is published under the **Functional Source License**
(FSL-1.1-ALv2). You may use it for any purpose **except offering Sunray as a
hosted or managed service that competes with our offerings**. Each released
version automatically converts to **Apache License 2.0** on the second
anniversary of its publication.

**Sunray Advanced Core (Sunray Enterprise — paid tier)** is published under
the **Elastic License 2.0**. You may use it for any purpose **except offering
it as a hosted or managed service**. Productive use additionally requires an
active commercial subscription with oursbl.eu (9€/month for 20 users + 1€ per
additional user ; "billed user" = user connecting ≥2 times per month).
Billing is currently inactive during beta — see [docs/licensing_decision.md](docs/licensing_decision.md).

## Beta status

Sunray is currently in beta. Billing is not yet active and runtime license
enforcement is on the roadmap. Source-available violations of the ELv2
commercial-subscription requirement are tolerated for the duration of beta
only ; this position will be reassessed when both billing and enforcement
go live.

## Manifest declarations

Odoo accepts only a closed vocabulary of `license` values in `__manifest__.py`.
We therefore use the closest matching standard value and direct readers to
this LICENSE file for the actual terms :

- `project_addons/sunray_core/__manifest__.py` declares `'Other OSI approved licence'` — actual license is **FSL-1.1-Apache-2.0**
- `project_addons_advanced/sunray_advanced_core/__manifest__.py` declares `'Other proprietary'` — actual license is **Elastic License 2.0**

## Distribution & IP

- **IP holder:** Cyril MORISSE (sole owner of all Sunray intellectual property)
- **Distributor:** oursbl.eu
- **Partner channel:** partners purchase commercial licenses at standard rates and resell their own hosting service — no white-label, no margin-sharing on the Sunray license fee

